{Project_1:[Project_1_Domain@@Project_1_2019 Transferred Fusion Learning using skipped networks .
Combining two pre-trained models to create a hybrid model. The idea here is that when we connect two models using skipped connections between layers of different models, each model can learn from the data as well as from each other.The project is currently under
progress and almost done.
]##Project_2:[Project_2_Domain@@Project_2_ 2019 Simple Social Media (as a cloud service) .
The project was to create a simple social media service with image support. We used flask to handle back-end and REST API for the communication between client and server. The server was hosted on AWS(Amazon Web Service) and had a load-balancer to control the
traffic.
]##Project_3:[Project_3_Domain@@Project_3_ 2019 Stock marked analysis using Machine Learning .
Stock market data data is actually time series. We used this data and extracted features (closing values of the stock). Different methods were used such as Linear Regression,
Auto-Arima, Prophet and LSTM to predict the stock value. LSTM was the best among them with accurate prediction.
]##Project_4:[Project_4_Domain@@Project_4_ 2019 Next word sequence prediction and Spell correction (NLP).
This project would basically make the computer text like humans with proper word choice and semantically correct sentences.A language model was built using LSTM to predict next sequence of words. Spell correction was done using Minimum edit distance algorithm.
]##Project_5:[Project_5_Domain@@Project_5_ 2018 Smart Home (voice control) .
This project consists of Raspberry pi, framework to define own commands, Google assistant and some Electronic devices. The output of Google assistant goes into the framework (IFTTT) which is connected to the Raspberry Pi. The R-pi keeps listening to the it and
receives appropriate signals. Based on the signal corresponding devices are controlled.]}

